Randy Vulakovich is an Republican member of the Pennsylvania House of Representatives for the 30th legislative district. He was first elected in 2006.[2] Prior to elective office, Vulakovich attended the Allegheny County Police Academy and Duquesne University.[3] He served as a police sergeant with the Shaler Township Police Department, where he was known by the affectionate moniker "Officer V. [4] On April 11, 2006, Democrat Shawn Flaherty defeated Republican Mike Dolan in a special election to fill the remainder of Jeff Habay's term as state representative.[5] On May 16, 2006 Vulakovich defeated two other Republicans (including Mike Dolan) for the right to challenge Flaherty in that November's election.[6] Vulakovich defeated Flaherty that November by a 53-47 margin.[2] Media related to Randy Vulakovich at Wikimedia Commons
